Narrator

Cameras flashed all around as my royal motorcade rolled up to the Iza University auditorium entrance.

Narrator

Vina had agreed to come along, with Manus as her date. The two of them were in the car behind mine.

Player_Romus

"Couldn't you have put on some makeup or something? You look ghastly."

Narrator

My daughter shrugged.

Narrator

The driver came around to open my door. I took a look out the window.

Narrator

Our heads were still missing.

Titus Gordion

"I don't think you should exit the car yet, Your Majesty."

Titus Gordion

"My scouts reported a number of individuals protesting near the entrance. A mix of students and foreigners, by the looks of it."

Narrator

Titus' voice came from the passenger seat.

Player_Romus

"Shit. Why haven't the police dealt with it?"

Player_Romus

"Su Omina is on the side of the Crown. Always has been."

Narrator

She smiled bleakly.

Player_Romus

"I should have expected this."

Titus Gordion

"Not anymore, apparently."

Titus Gordion

"It doesn't bode well for your own health."

Titus Gordion

"The fact that local law enforcement hasn't stepped in is troubling."

Player_Romus

"Obviously. Use as much force as you need."

Player_Romus

"Seems like we're getting a warmer welcome than last time."

Player_Romus

"Are you sure? I don't want any unpleasant surprises."

Titus Gordion

"Rest assured local law enforcement is doing its job."

Titus Gordion

"I'm pleased local law enforcement is doing its job."

Narrator

Titus and his guards shielded Vina and me as we walked through the roiling crowd.

Narrator

I heard shouts of "Rights for all!" and "Down with House Toras!"

Narrator

Titus and his guards shielded me as we walked through the roiling crowd.

Narrator

They rose and cheered enthusiastically as I proceeded down the hall.

Narrator

I was halfway to the stage when the hall erupted into cheers. I turned my head to see Manus Sazon waving to the crowd.

Narrator

I took my place on stage next to Rico. He was seated with his legs spread out, his expression radiating barely concealed disdain.

Titus Gordion

"Of course, Your Majesty."

Narrator

Plainclothes police officers guarded the building doors. They saluted me as I went inside.

Player_Romus

"I got quite the reception on my way in. You had better have an explanation."

Player_Romus

"Let's get this over with, eh?"

Narrator

Vina split off for the front row as I took my place on stage next to Rico. He was seated with his legs spread out, his expression radiating barely concealed disdain.

Narrator

I heard shouts of "Rights for all!" and "Stop the war!"

Rico Toras

"Good bloody riddance. And I do mean bloody."

Rico Toras

"Sorry, cousin. But the police you sent me are completely useless."

Rico Toras

"Sorry, cousin. I tried to tell Su Omina to rein it in, but, well. You know how they get."

Player_Romus

"Shit. Why haven't the police dealt with it?"

Vina Toras

"Because they're outnumbered."

Player_Romus

"Looking pretty peaceful around here these days."

Rico Toras

"Don't let looks deceive you, Your Majesty."

Rico Toras

"I had my doubts about those Central Police reinforcements you sent. But they've really helped me get Iza into shape."

Rico Toras

"They don't respect me around here. I don't see why I should respect them."

Rico Toras

"But as His Majesty commands."

Rico Toras

"I'm wondering whether I should have even bothered coming here."

Rico Toras

"This whole place is a hotbed of rebellion. Even after we arrested half the professors."

Narrator

After a short presentation about the history of the university, she invited the Duke of Iza to speak.

Narrator

Titus went to stand guard in the wings. He had a radio pressed to his ear and a look of concentration on his face.

Narrator

Nobody clapped as Rico took the stage.

Rico Toras

"I must confess to you all, the only higher education I've received is from the School of Life. And I haven't even graduated yet."

Rico Toras

"But when I took charge of Iza, I realized what an important role this institution plays."

Rico Toras

"But I expect you knew that already, Your Majesty."

Narrator

His voice assumed an icy tone.

Rico Toras

"At least the students won't give us much trouble. Not with most of of the boys fighting in Pales."

Rico Toras

"Iza University was founded in order to preserve our kingdom's cherished traditions and pass them on to the next generation."

Rico Toras

"To instill young people like yourselves with a stable moral center, even when one is lacking outside these walls."

Rico Toras

"But somehow, over the years, that purpose was lost."

Rico Toras

"And where youths respond to the harsh reality of war not by rising to defend their nation, but by waving signs and chanting."

Rico Toras

"This isn't education. It's indoctrination."

Narrator

He leveled his gaze out at the audience.

Narrator

A few students began booing. Rico ignored them.

Rico Toras

"See, this is exactly what I mean."

Player_Romus

"Ha! Try and study your way out of that!"

Narrator

The Su Omina members gave Rico a questioning look. After a few long moments, he nodded.

Narrator

Rico watched with a small smile on his face. Once the door had closed, he continued.

Narrator

All at once, the people sitting in the back row stood up. They were all wearing military-style jackets with patches bearing the Su Omina insignia.

Narrator

The crowd erupted into fury.

Narrator

A student sitting near the front yelled "Fascist!". Rico jerked his head in her direction.

Narrator

Nobody laughed. Rico frowned and continued.

Rico Toras

"Now, if I actually were fascist, do you think I'd let this young lady make it out of this auditorium alive?"

Player_Romus

"Rico, get off the stage. It's time for the King to speak."

Player_Romus

"STOP THIS NONSENSE AT ONCE!"

Narrator

Rico opened his mouth to retort, then closed it. He nodded his assent.

Narrator

Their boos escalated into full-throated shouts of "Down with the Duke!"

Player_Romus

"Then do it yourself."

Narrator

The audience began cheering as he retreated from the podium. He spoke to me under his breath.

Narrator

After a few minutes, the crowd was silent again.

Player_Romus

"You will allow your Duke to finish his speech."

Narrator

After a minute or so, the shouts subsided.

Player_Romus_Italic

I said nothing and waited for Rico to act.

Rico Toras

"That little interruption just proved my point."

Player_Romus

"That's enough, Rico. It's time for the King to speak."

Player_Romus

"There will be no other interruptions. Let the Duke of Iza finish his speech."

Rico Toras

"If we are to persevere as a kingdom, we cannot allow the minds of our youths to become clouded by dissent and division."

Rico Toras

"And we must be ready to defend our identity as Rizians at all costs, be it on the battlefield or in the lecture hall."

Rico Toras

"Thank you, Your Majesty."

Narrator

His eyes filled with fury. He reluctantly nodded his assent.

Rico Toras

"Which is why I urge you to use this occasion to come together as Rizians. To rejoice in the proud history of our kingdom, and look forward to its shining future."

Player_Romus

"That interruption should never have happened in the first place."

Rico Toras

"Where 'intellectual freedom' is encouraged but patriotism is silenced."

Rico Toras

"Where we are forced to discard our centuries-old spiritual practices in the name of 'inclusivity'."

Narrator

The audience had started speaking in hushed whispers. They quieted down as I took Rico's place behind the podium.

Rico Toras

"You see what I'm up against. I doubt you'll fare much better."

Player_Romus

"You brought this on yourself, cousin. You embarrassed us both."

Narrator

Moving in unison, they marched down the aisle towards the student who'd shouted and roughly yanked her out of her seat.

Rico Toras

"I may not be a man of letters, but I do know you can't spell 'university' without 'unity'."

Rico Toras

"Glovurius axa Rizia, God save King Romus, and God bless our troops. Thank you."

Narrator

I glanced at Titus. He had his ear to his radio again.

Player_Romus

"Ladies and gentlemen of Iza."

Player_Romus

"My fellow cacti."

Player_Romus

"Dear brothers and sisters."

Player_Romus

"My loyal subjects."

Player_Romus

"My fellow Rizians."

Narrator

They rose and bowed politely as I proceeded down the hall.

Narrator

A few students whooped.

Player_Romus

"I am proud to be an alumnus of the oldest and most prestigious university in Rizia."

Player_Romus

"This is truly our kingdom's greatest institute of higher learning -- besides my own Romus Toras University, of course."

Player_Romus

"War, revolution, social upheaval -- these halls have seen it all and lived to tell the tale."

Player_Romus

"I apologize for the earlier interruption. It was unbefitting of this momentous occasion."

Player_Romus

"750 years. What a milestone -- not only for this university, but for Rizia."

Player_Romus

"After nearly a millennium, Iza University remains a beacon of freedom in a kingdom that has so rarely enjoyed it."

Player_Romus

"And so it gives me no great pleasure to see how far this school and the city around it have fallen."

Player_Romus

"Which is why I am truly dismayed that the Duke of Iza has allowed a culture of hate and intolerance to pervade this place."

Player_Romus

"The fact that the university has persevered for so long is testament to the strength of this kingdom, its rulers and its people."

Player_Romus

"And I am overjoyed to see how this school and the city around it have flourished under House Toras' leadership."

Player_Romus

"I know that Iza still bears the psychic scars of Lucas Sazon's unforgivable betrayal, just as my body bears the physical ones."

Player_Romus

"And I sincerely regret that, for nearly 30 years, the bright minds residing here have had to suffer under the thumb of House Toras."

Player_Romus

"I look at you all and I see the future that I want this country to have. Diverse, curious, unafraid to question authority."

Player_Romus

"In another era, you would all be beheaded for such flagrant disobedience of your reigning Duke."

Player_Romus

"I know that Iza still bears the psychic scars of Lucas Sazon's unforgivable betrayal."

Player_Romus

"It is one thing to speak against your Duke. It is another to speak against House Toras."

Narrator

Rico was staring daggers at me. The Su Omina members in the audience shifted in their seats uneasily.

Player_Romus

"I understand the allure of an organization like Su Omina. But it is not the answer."

Player_Romus

"He speaks of unity, yet seeks to draw arbitrary lines between 'us' and 'them'."

Narrator

Vina's eyes were burning holes in my head.

Player_Romus

"My family took it upon ourselves to keep the peace here after Duke and Duchess Sazon were deposed. I'm afraid we have failed."

Player_Romus

"I hereby call for the arrest of Duke Ricardus Toras for his role in the Friendship Day incident of 1950."

Player_Romus

"But I cannot only blame you. My cousin has failed miserably in his duties as a ruler."

Player_Romus

"Iza still bears the psychic scars of the Sazon family's betrayal. Yet my cousin's rein has been punishment enough."

Player_Romus

"I hereby announce that I am ordering his removal as Duke, as well as his immediate arrest."

Narrator

The audience roared. Rico's jaw dropped open in disbelief.

Player_Romus

"Captain Gordion, arrest this man."

Player_Romus

"He will be extradited to Wehlen for his role in the bloodshed."

Player_Romus

"Look at the progress we've made over the past few years. Do we want that to be undermined?"

Player_Romus

"For too long, nobles like my cousin have lived off the labor of foreigners and commoners while treating them as an inconvenience at best."

Narrator

The audience broke into animated chatter. Rico was staring daggers at me.

Player_Romus

"My grandmother Lyza was right. Our identity as Rizians is defined not by our nationality, but by our loyalty to the Crown."

Narrator

Rico looked agitated. His eyes darted back and forth from me to the audience.

Player_Romus

"I did not want to do this here. But I must tell you that my cousin was behind the horrific attack in Zille five years ago."

Player_Romus

"In times of war, displaying insubordination towards your ruling house is tantamount to treason."

Player_Romus

"You will doom this kingdom with your insubordination."

Narrator

A shout of "Justice for Manus!" came from somewhere in the crowd.

Player_Romus

"I know that Iza still bears the psychic scars of Lucas Sazon's unforgivable betrayal."

Player_Romus

"I must especially commend my cousin Ricardus for showing exceptional leadership in the face of turmoil."

Player_Romus

"Having said that, I must admit my family made a mistake in installing Ricardus Toras as your Duke."

Narrator

The Su Omina members in the audience applauded loudly.

Player_Romus

"I am grateful to the members of House Sazon for their contributions to this kingdom. But their time is over. A new era has dawned."

Player_Romus

"This city must serve as an example for the rest of Rizia. Those who speak against their rulers will receive their just desserts."

Player_Romus

"Over and over again, he has failed to display the backbone needed to get this city in line."

Player_Romus

"When law enforcement does not play by his rules, he calls on disgruntled civilians to restore order."

Narrator

The Su Omina members in the audience began booing.

Player_Romus

"I will tell you the truth. Rico Toras is a criminal and a conspirator. Were it not for him, we would have Zille back by now."

Player_Romus

"You should be receiving an education here. Instead, you are being brainwashed by Arcasian agents."

Player_Romus

"I can only hope that now that Iza has been leached of the poison that is House Sazon, you will be able to redeem yourselves."

Narrator

Nobody dared to speak.

Player_Romus

"Manus Sazon has received exactly the justice he deserves."

Player_Romus

"I will give you one last chance. You will bend the knee to House Toras or face the direst of consequences."

Player_Romus

"Our kingdom is at a turning point. We are finally on the verge of claiming our lost territories and becoming whole again."

Narrator

Titus and his fellow Golden Guards moved swiftly to intercept them.

Narrator

As Titus handcuffed my cousin and led him offstage, the audience burst into thunderous applause.

Player_Romus

"Return to your seats at once!"

Narrator

Once the commotion had died down, I continued.

Narrator

Once they were completely out of sight, I continued.

Rico Toras

"My father will not stand for this, Your Majesty."

Rico Toras

"My father will not stand for this."

Narrator

The other Su Omina members scattered as Titus' guards swiftly approached my cousin. Rico's eyes locked on to mine.

Player_Romus

"You're welcome, Iza."

Player_Romus

"I regret that you all had to witness that."

Player_Romus

"As your king, it falls upon me to name my cousin's replacement."

Player_Romus

"I do not wish to shift the focus from today's celebrations. But I will say this."

Player_Romus

"I have pardoned the Duchess of Iza, Angelica Sazon. I now call upon her to resume governorship of her rightful home, which shall be transferred back to the province of Brenas."

Player_Romus

"Iza will no longer have a Duke. It will be reincorporated into Brenas and governed by its own democratically elected council."

Player_Romus

"For now, there will be no new Duke. Iza will remain under Rizia Imperii's jurisdiction, overseen by the central government."

Player_Romus

"I am placing Iza under police rule to ensure order and public safety. A new Duke will be appointed if and when stability is restored."

Narrator

A hush came over the crowd as my announcement sank in.

Narrator

A hush came over the crowd as my announcement sank in.

Narrator

The students and teachers assembled rose and began clapping.

Narrator

Vina and Manus rose to their feet and applauded as well.

Player_Romus

"My reign is all about breaking away from the constraints of the past. It is time for Iza to do exactly that."

Player_Romus

"Your current Duke is a disgrace to everything the noble House Toras stands for."

Player_Romus

"What I love most about this school is its diversity of opinions. Yes, even anti-monarchist ones."

Player_Romus

"When you graduate and go forth into the world, I want you to keep questioning authority. Including mine."

Player_Romus

"Your voices matter to me. You are the future of this country, after all."

Player_Romus

"Radical thinking is in Iza's blood. It even resulted in the spilling of mine."

Player_Romus

"You turn your blame on myself and my cousin while ignoring the real enemy. The foreigners at our doorstep."

Player_Romus

"You turn your blame on myself and my cousin while ignoring the real enemy. Pales."

Player_Romus

"I have heard your calls for a change in leadership. And I am taking them very seriously."

Player_Romus

"I am asking you to be patient. The change you want to see is coming to Rizia. But it will take time."

Player_Romus

"But I beg you to consider the consequences of your actions. The revolution you are calling for would only bring destruction to you and your loved ones."

Player_Romus

"I agree that Rico Toras should never have been handed the key to Iza."

Player_Romus

"But the challenges our nation is facing are greater than any of our individual concerns. Now is not the time to let petty differences tear us apart."

Player_Romus

"But in the end, the governance of Iza is the noble right -- and the burden -- of House Toras."

Player_Romus

"However, I have determined that at this time, my cousin Ricardus is still the best choice to govern this city."

Player_Romus

"You're lucky that your king is listening to you at all! In an earlier era, I'd have you beheaded."

Player_Romus

"Stop complaining, dammit! I am on your side!"

Narrator

A group of students in the middle row of seats stood up simultaneously.

Player_Romus

"Your king commands you to get back in your seats!"

Player_Romus

"Stop them, Titus."

Player_Romus

"That's right! Don't underestimate the power of peaceful protest!"

Narrator

They removed their jackets to reveal white shirts with letters printed on them.

Narrator

They removed their jackets to reveal white shirts with letters printed on them.

Player_Romus

"Police! Do something!"

Narrator

Nobody listened.

Narrator

The Brenas police officers didn't budge.

Narrator

Only a few people remained seated. One of them was Vina.

Narrator

Holding eye contact with me, she elegantly rose from her chair, turned around and left the room as well.

Narrator

Only a few people remained seated. Vina and Manus were among them.

Narrator

At the same time, they both rose from their chairs, turned around and left the room as well.

Narrator

Holding eye contact with me, he rose from his chair, turned around and left the room as well.

Player_Romus

"Our kingdom is at a turning point. We face countless enemies, and the most dangerous of all are those within our own borders."

Player_Romus

"These are perilous times. We are at risk of being destroyed by the nefarious forces outside our door."

Player_Romus

"Our enemies tried to destroy us from within in the '20s. Little did they know Rizia would end up stronger than ever."

Player_Romus

"I am relying on you all to uphold Rizia's reputation."

Player_Romus

"With God on our side, we will overcome every challenge."

Player_Romus

"I implore you to hold fast to your Rizian identity. Remember the values upon which this nation was built."

Player_Romus

"Time and time again, the Toras family has led Rizia out of crisis. With your help, we will do so again."

Player_Romus

"If you learn one thing here, it should be to trust in the superiority of your King and your ruling house."

Player_Romus

"I promise you, we will prosper as never before!"

Player_Romus

"We will restore the glory days of our golden kingdom!"

Player_Romus

"Glovurius axa Rizia!"

Player_Romus

"You may clap now."

Player_Romus

"God bless you all, and God bless Rizia!"

Player_Romus

"Lead the way. I'm done with this shitshow."

Player_Romus

"No, I want to see what happens. I am staying."

Player_Romus

"Get Vina out, too. She could be in danger."

Player_Romus

"All right. If you insist."

Titus Gordion

"If you're sure..."

Titus Gordion

"Come on."

Narrator

He gestured to Vina. She shook her head.

Narrator

I could still hear the sound of shouts and fistfights as Rico and I followed Titus and his guards through the back door.

Narrator

A shot suddenly rang out, followed by ear-splitting cries.

Narrator

Titus grabbed my wrist. I saw his men do the same with Vina.

Player_Romus

"I would therefore like to announce that I am removing Ricardus Toras from power. Effective immediately."

Narrator

Titus grabbed his shoulders and forced him back into his chair.

Narrator

Many wore outfits adorned with the Iza University mascot, an anthropomorphic cactus named Spikey.

Narrator

The protesters surged towards the blocked doors.

Narrator

By sheer numbers, they managed to overpower the guards and squeeze out of the building.

Titus Gordion

"We have to get you out of here. There's a back exit."

Narrator

The university dean was still on stage with us. She looked at me questioningly.

Player_Romus

"This is more than just student hijinks. Our international enemies have had a hand in it."

Player_Romus

"A little rebellion is normal at that age. Nothing to be worried about."

Rico Toras

"What *I've* done? Your Majesty--"

Rico Toras

"If you'd just given me the resources to do my job--"

Rico Toras

"But never mind. It's too late."

Narrator

As we left the building, the splatters of red on the students' shirts remained seared into my consciousness.

Narrator

As we left the building, the capital letters on the students' shirts remained seared into my consciousness.

Narrator

A hush came over the crowd as my announcement sank in.

Narrator

Hesitantly, the students and teachers assembled began clapping.

Narrator

Vina and Manus both sat still. They weren't applauding at all.

Narrator

Manus sat still. He wasn't applauding at all.

Narrator

The House Sazon nobles in the audience applauded politely. I saw steel in their eyes.

Narrator

With fear in their eyes, the students and teachers assembled began clapping.

Player_Romus

"Rejoice, Iza! You are finally free!"

Player_Romus

"Glovurius axa Rizia!"

Narrator

The auditorium reverberated with thunderous applause.

Narrator

I looked over once more at the empty seat where Rico had been.

Narrator

But with House Sazon on my side, perhaps I could still weather the storm.

Player_Romus

"Power to the people!"

Player_Romus

"Long live the King!"

Narrator

But with the people on my side, perhaps I could still weather the storm.

Narrator

I sat back down next to Rico.

Player_Romus

"I am quite the compelling public speaker, aren't I?"

Player_Romus

"I was just repairing the damage from your speech."

Rico Toras

"One person got upset. Everyone else loved me."

Player_Romus

"I'm just happy that I can go home now."

Narrator

It sounded like the voice of the student who had been dragged away by Su Omina earlier.

Player_Romus

"Still, I ask you to have patience. Your duke is young, and has much to learn."

Player_Romus

"I have heard your calls for a change of leadership in this city. And I take them seriously."

Player_Romus

"I have faith that the good city of Iza will embrace peace and progress. Even with Duke Ricardus nominally holding the reins."

Player_Romus

"My cousin is a tiger without teeth or claws. Leave him his title, and you can have the rest."

Player_Romus

"And yes, that 'authority' includes your own duke."

Player_Romus

"You are even willing to stand up to your own king."

Player_Romus

"Even in a city where fanatical supremacists are allowed to run rampant, you stand your ground."

Player_Romus

"You are coming of age in an era where ordinary Rizians are allowed more representation than ever before."

Player_Romus

"But we can't forget our history and heritage, even as we hurtle into tomorrow."

Player_Romus

"It is places like Iza that represent the values that our country is fighting for."

Player_Romus

"Yet there are people who stubbornly cling to the unfair hierarchies and constrictive labels of the past."

Player_Romus

"Once we have reconquered Pales, I will turn my attention to the restructuring of Iza's government."

Player_Romus

"Change is at your fingertips. All you need to do is reach out and grasp it."

Player_Romus

"You, the people of Iza, have what it takes to rise up against your oppressors."

Player_Romus

"You have voted in a city council that prioritizes the rights of the previously disenfranchised. Use it."

Player_Romus

"Have faith in your ruling house. It may take time, but order will prevail."

Player_Romus

"My cousin is not the problem. It is the flawed system that put him in power."

Narrator

The audience tittered in astonishment. Rico looked even more uncomfortable.

Narrator

Someone in the audience yelled, "Now!".

Player_Romus

"Perhaps all of you can learn together what it means to coexist."

Narrator

My remark was greeted by sullen silence.

Player_Romus

"We must find a way to reconcile tradition and modernity. Just as this fine university has done."

Narrator

There was a smattering of polite applause.

Player_Romus

"Remember, knowledge is your most powerful weapon."

Player_Romus

"Do not underestimate the power of organization. Together, you are greater than the sum of your parts."

Player_Romus

"Do not fall victim to calls for violence. The path of peace will get you further than you expect."

Player_Romus

"I have given you the tools to break free of your chains. It is up to you to use them."

Player_Romus

"God bless you all!"

Player_Romus

"Goooo Fighting Cacti!"

Player_Romus

"The King has spoken!"

Narrator

Vina rose from her seat and began clapping. There was steel in her eyes.

Narrator

Vina and Manus immediately rose from their seats and began clapping.

Narrator

Manus rose from his seat and began clapping. There was steel in his eyes.

Rico Toras

"Forgive me, Your Majesty, but... what the hell was that?"

Player_Romus

"You should be grateful. It was either that or have you deposed."

Player_Romus

"A dose of the truth. Take it or leave it."

Player_Romus

"Just putting on a show for the kids. Don't worry, your job is safe."

Rico Toras

"I'm as good as deposed now."

Narrator

The applause continued as we left our seats and headed toward the banquet that had been prepared in our honor.

Narrator

Rico was right. Hugo wouldn't stand for this.

Player_Romus

"I implore you to hold fast to your identity. Remember the values upon which this nation was built. Only then can we find a way forward."

Player_Romus

"Time and time again, the Toras family has led Rizia out of crisis. With your help, we will do so again."

Player_Romus

"Rizian, Wehzek, Derdian, Valgish -- I call on all subjects of the Crown to unite as one."

Player_Romus

"In times of instability, it is crucial we respect our established structures, even if we don't agree with them."

Player_Romus

"I ask you to engage in constructive discourse. Do not abandon your convictions, but do not give in to the path of violence, either."

Player_Romus

"Glovurius axa Rizia!"

Player_Romus

"God bless you all!"

Player_Romus

"The King has spoken!"

Narrator

Vina sat still. She wasn't applauding at all.

Narrator

Vina and Manus both sat still. They weren't applauding at all.

Narrator

Manus sat still. He wasn't applauding at all.

Rico Toras

"That was... interesting, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"I'm just glad it's over. I can't wait to go home."

Player_Romus

"At least nobody called me a fascist."

Player_Romus

"It was either that or have you deposed. Be grateful."

Rico Toras

"Same here."

Rico Toras

"You could've tried harder to please your own family."

Narrator

The celebratory speeches wrapped up, and Titus and his guards escorted us out of the auditorium's back entrance.

Narrator

As we were exiting, I noticed a van parked around the corner from the building. Muffled screams were emanating from it.
